<UserControl x:Class="Ajubaa.IBModeler.Help.DialogHelps.AdjustSkinDialog"
             xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
             xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006" 
             xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008" 
             mc:Ignorable="d" 
             d:DesignHeight="600" d:DesignWidth="600">
    <UserControl.Resources>
        <ResourceDictionary>
            <ResourceDictionary.MergedDictionaries>
                <ResourceDictionary Source="..\Resources\TextStyles.xaml"/>
            </ResourceDictionary.MergedDictionaries>
        </ResourceDictionary>
    </UserControl.Resources>
    <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource UsualText}" TextWrapping="Wrap" Margin="10">
        <TextBlock TextDecorations="Underline">Adjust Skin</TextBlock>
        <LineBreak/>
        This option is available when you use 4 corner photos as model skin. If you
        <LineBreak/>
        find that some images overlap, you can fix it by reducing the area of each
        <LineBreak/>
        image in the skin.
        <LineBreak/>
        <LineBreak/>
        Typically, the skin values for each photo can be anywhere between 0 to 1.
        <LineBreak/>
        The actual values for the given model are shown in the dialog.
        <LineBreak/>
        <LineBreak/>
        You can move the sliders for each photo to reduce these values to get a 
        <LineBreak/>
        better fitting skin.
        <LineBreak/>
        <LineBreak/>
        The below diagram illustrates how these values are set for each photo:
        <LineBreak/>  
        <Image Margin="0,5,0,0" HorizontalAlignment="Center" Width="200" Source="pack://application:,,,/Ajubaa.IBModeler.Help;component/images/adjust_skin_help.png" />
    </TextBlock>
</UserControl>
